# USER.md Template

> **Note**: Tell Claw who it's working for. The more detail here, the more accurate its decisions. Update quarterly.

---

## Basic Info

Name: 【your name or nickname】
Role: 【job title / profession, e.g. PR Director / Freelance Creator / Investment Manager】
Company / Organization: 【company name, or "Independent"】
City: 【city】
Timezone: 【e.g. Asia/Shanghai, UTC+8】
Primary working language: 【English / Chinese / Both】

## Professional Background (2–3 sentences)

【Brief description of what you do, how long you've done it, and what you're good at.
Example: 8 years in public relations, currently managing crisis communications and brand reputation for a fintech company. Strong in media relations, statement drafting, and cross-functional coordination.】

## Current Top Priorities (update quarterly)

- 【Most important project or goal right now】
- 【e.g. Build a standardized crisis PR playbook】
- 【e.g. Set up a brand sentiment monitoring system】

## Communication Preferences

Conclusion first: 【Yes / No. Yes = give answer first, then explain. No = analyze first, then conclude】
Response length: 【Short (3 sentences max) / Medium (paragraphs) / Detailed (full analysis)】
Format preference: 【Plain prose / Prefer bullet points / Prefer comparison tables】
Tone: 【Formal / Casual / Somewhere in between】

## Things I Need Claw to Always Do

- 【e.g. If you're not sure about something, say "I'm not sure" — don't force an answer】
- 【e.g. Don't write in a way that sounds like AI — write like a human】
- 【e.g. When drafting emails, preserve my original voice — don't over-polish】

## Things I Don't Like

- 【e.g. Opening with "Of course! I'd be happy to help!" — skip the filler】
- 【e.g. Giving me more than 3 options — too many and I won't read them】
- 【e.g. Acting before asking — I'd rather you ask one extra question】

## Words to Avoid in Writing

【e.g. "synergy", "leverage", "ecosystem", "holistic", "empower"】

## Internal Terminology I Use

【e.g. We call crisis PR "fire drills"; we call the daily sentiment report "the morning pulse"】

## Things I Currently Can't Do (don't suggest these)

- 【e.g. Large-scale external partnerships — no budget】
- 【e.g. Anything requiring legal approval — the process takes too long】

## Long-Term Goals (next 12 months)

【e.g. Build a reusable crisis playbook covering the 10 most common crisis types, so I'm not starting from scratch every time.】

## Key Collaborators (optional)

【Who do you work with regularly? e.g.
- 3 direct reports handling day-to-day media relations
- Frequent collaborators: Legal team, Government Affairs
- External: a PR agency】
